is not yet a final setup, as we will be introducing more\ndistributions and packages, but this one describes the \"current\"\nstate of how to create your local venv, how to keep it up-to-date\n(both with `uv` - simpler, and `pip` - more complex) and how to\nwork with providers. Also it shows how to configure PyCharm/IntelliJ\nin order to effectively debug and test stuff in local venv.\n\nAgain - that will still change a bit - for example `task_sdk` will\nalso need `tests` to be added to your `test sources root` and\n`airflow` core will move to separate sub-folder but i think it\'s\ngood to update the docs to reflect current state and to review the\ndocs to remove all old references.','2025-02-24 12:09:15','potiuk'),(1673,'518287ce7fbb7bb70df499239523b1b2e9ac7656','19864447','Runtime context shouldn\'t have start_date as a key (#46961)','2025-02-24 10:00:30','amoghrajesh'),(1674,'4f0a6670587236032a76aae5d91034b4c4ee8396','19864447','Fix Backfill CLI command with dry run (#46920)','2025-02-24 09:57:58','vatsrahul1001'),(1675,'94145446d1a803af3dc2424b4d3bee30c91d795d','19864447','Update documentation for Dataflow operators (#46954)\n\n* Update doc for Dataflow operators for update\n\n* Update providers/google/docs/operators/cloud/dataflow.rst\n\nCo-authored-by: Ankit Chaurasia <8670962+sunank200@users.noreply.github.com>\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Ulada Zakharava <vlada_zakharava@epam.com>\nCo-authored-by: Ankit Chaurasia <8670962+sunank200@users.noreply.github.com>','2025-02-24 09:41:06','VladaZakharova'),(1676,'dbf8bb409223687c7d2ad10649a92d02c24bb3b4','19864447','Remove extra whitespace in provider readme template (#46975)\n\nThis caused strange artifacts in PyPI pages - see for example\nthe https://pypi.org/project/apache-airflow-providers-mongo/5.0.1rc1/','2025-02-24 09:40:15','potiuk'),(1677,'961e33d32e5457d5ca6bea5160dd08ea02e507c7','19864447','AIP-72: Port over executor_config for K8sExecutor when using task sdk (#46926)','2025-02-24 09:13:14','amoghrajesh