t verify_integrity is not called for versioned bundle\r\n\r\n* order dagrun.version_number correctly\r\n\r\n* join load task_instances when examining running dagruns','2025-02-18 12:19:02','ephraimbuddy'),(1746,'b715909ef1caf499b52ba86e14d8c5eb7859ecde','19864447','fix test using time travel (#46859)','2025-02-18 11:21:01','vatsrahul1001'),(1747,'8c374a89c7c4713e1cc5512ab7467c6aa90f4110','19864447','Handle None in DagRunAssetReference (#46847)\n\nThree fields can be None: logical_date, data_interval_start, and\r\ndata_interval_end.','2025-02-18 10:46:48','uranusjr'),(1748,'18396ed8083f38eebe7db062110d8c569cb4fa3d','19864447','Rework the TriggererJobRunner to run triggers in a process without DB access (#46677)\n\nThis uses a similar approach to the DAG Parser -- the subprocess runs the async\nTriggers (i.e. user code) in a process and sends messages back and forth to the\nsupervisor/parent to perform CRUD operations on the DB.\n\nI have also massively re-worked how per-trigger logging works to greatly\nsimplify it. I hope @dstandish will approve. The main way it has been\nsimplified is with the switch to TaskSDK then _all_ (100%! Really) of logs are\nset as JSON over a socket to the parent process; everything in the subprocess\nlogs to this output, there is no differentiation needed in stdlib, no custom\nhandlers etc. and by making use of structlog\'s automatic context vars we can\ninclude a trigger_id field -- if we find that we route the output to the right\ntrigger specific log file.\n\nThis is all now so much simpler with structlog in the mix.\n\nLogging from the async process works as follows:\n- stdlib logging is configured to send messages via struct log as json\n- As part of the stdlib->structlog processing change we include structlog bound\n  contextvars\n- When a triggerer coro starts it binds `trigger_id` as a paramter\n- When the Supervisor receives a log message (which happens as LD JSON over a\n  dedicated  socket channel) it parses the JSON, and if it finds `trigger_id`\n  key in there it redirects it to the trigger file log, else prints it.\n\nOf note: I haven\'t allowed triggers to directly access or set Xcom, Variables\netc. We can add that in future if there is demand.','2025-02-18 09:39:31','ashb'),(1749,'8fbdf75dc7e536f55d07965254f800d181afa2b7','19864447','Excluding system tests from dag serialisation tests (#46850)','2025-02-18 04:48:10','amoghrajesh'),(1750,'fdbd68f02e86dcfec20178d3309b7398cb43ce32','19864447','TriggerDagRunOperator by defaults set logical date as null (#46633)\n\n* TriggerDagRunOperator can now will have default null as logical date\r\n\r\n* refactor deferrable code and also fix TriggerDagRunOperator tests\r\n\r\n* fix test_external_task.py\r\n\r\n* fix external_task tests + run_id changes in WorkflowTrigger\r\n\r\n* fix test_external_tasks\r\n\r\n* implementent review comments + fix 2.9 tests\r\n\r\n* fix test_external_tasks\r\n\r\n* fix static checks\r\n\r\n* fix test failure for mysql and sqlite\r\n\r\n* update dag_run_id in tests','2025-02-18 03:38:17','vatsrahul1001'),(1751,'c4091ab02e4e95cc930fefde5af3120cfdaec7dc','19864447','Remove tests from example_dags folder (#46819)\n\nCo-authored-by: Ulada Zakharava <vlada_zakharava@epam.com>','2025-02-17 22:52:36','VladaZakharova'),(1752,'fece9c7dfc5f496dd673ce394a8e742a4f6e3866','19864447','Create operators for working with Clusters for GCP Apache Kafka (#45795)','2025-02-17 22:44:47','MaksYermak'),(1753,'165ea9ed0c42d1dc06b373e62a5c6cbaa27b5633','19864447','[EDGE]CLI allows to retrieve status of worker (#46818)\n\n* CLI allows to retrieve status of worker\n\n* make jobs static\n\n* fix static checks\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Majoros Donat (XC-DX/EET2-Bp) <donat.majoros2@hu.bosch.com>','2025-02-17 21:47:48','majorosdonat'),(1754,'4c786c42dd68b656a9434a0b0bc27760134e53c6','19864447','Deprecate old bigquery operators and introduce CreateTableOperator (#46673)\n\nCo-authored-by: Ulada Zakharava <vlada_zakharava@epam.com>','2025-02-17