ean provider released in earlier than mid 2023 won\'t\nwork with Airflow 3 (and I\'d imagine there will be other reasons they\nwont work as well).','2024-12-12 16:52:02','jedcunningham'),(2968,'67cff1577ee9c334a3c52cd9cdbccf2fc7a61ee1','19864447','Refactor documentation modal component to use it for dag and task. (#44863)\n\n* Refactor documentation modal component to use it for dag and task.\r\n\r\n* Refactor to pass doc type directly instead of using a boolean.','2024-12-12 15:41:05','tirkarthi'),(2969,'39d79fc513bd2fc365107a906f609d6a9f8909c1','19864447','Hide UI list backfills from documentation (#44871)\n\n* Hide UI list backfills from documentation\r\n\r\n* Move to the router definition','2024-12-12 15:33:51','pierrejeambrun'),(2970,'a6064f3a3c74cd1c1de7a044672d60b84da4252b','19864447','Handle the next URL after logging in in the simple auth manager (#44856)','2024-12-12 14:59:57','vincbeck'),(2971,'f585a8016bcf4622eb0e7076fde3c49e9ac50d18','19864447','Restructure WatchedSubprocess and CommsDecoder for reuse in DagParsing (#44874)\n\nThe changes introduced here lets these existing classes serve \"double\" duty in\r\nthe execution time of TaskSDK and also the Parse Time in the DAG Processor\r\n(but the actual switch to use these will be a separate bigger PR).\r\n\r\nThere are a few warts here, namely:\r\n\r\n- The default on `CommsDecoder`\'s decoder argument is incorrect for\r\n  subclasses, we might fix that later to be more dynamic about the default.\r\n- The location of this code is not right for reuse in TaskSDK/execution time\r\n  and parse time. There is a bigger bit of work being planned to move this all\r\n  around before release of Airflow 3\r\n- Some of the functions on the base WatchedSubprocess class are TI specific\r\n  and maybe should be on a separate subclass','2024-12-12 14:04:04','ashb'),(2972,'b7df4639b5b61cca0b5bac7687f1d6e6e4c6c40a','19864447','Update trigger_timeout column in task_instance table to use UtcDateTime (#44507)\n\n* update task instance trigger timeout to utcdatetime\r\n\r\n* update task instance trigger timeout to utcdatetime\r\n\r\n* update task instance trigger timeout to utcdatetime\r\n\r\n* updatng task_instance file\r\n\r\n* update migration desc\r\n\r\n* fixing execution api test\r\n\r\n* adding migration condition to run only for postgresql\r\n\r\n* fix static check\r\n\r\n* remove postgresql condition','2024-12-12 11:34:27','vatsrahul1001'),(2973,'3e2b5e2f54ea3b3695e6576313f87460fb098830','19864447','Fixing rendering of Airflow RC testing email links (#44862)','2024-12-12 05:58:09','amoghrajesh'),(2974,'04011f329ea006abdfa2d7c644eff1b10c9dc27b','19864447','Fetch recent dag runs using dag id instead of dag display pattern. (#44861)','2024-12-12 04:29:29','tirkarthi'),(2975,'b5c7057d3d586f3fdd8273b1b61557c2db44fa6c','19864447','Bump `uv` to `0.5.8` (#44851)\n\nhttps://pypi.org/project/uv/0.5.8/','2024-12-11 20:31:41','kaxil'),(2976,'410b93083bb2d9889d8acc495513328f81b49794','19864447','Add Task Details page (#44828)\n\n* Add Task Details page\r\n\r\n* Fix sorts and links','2024-12-11 18:05:34','bbovenzi'),(2977,'9aa2cea953480ef69f950d6d82088ad81b509287','19864447','Remove unused `dag_ids` argument to DagFile processor classes. (#44845)\n\nThis hasn\'t been possible to set in a while, (like since sometime before 2.0,\npossibly even before 1.8) and the doc string gives a clue to the behaviour:\nonly to schedule certain dags, but that is not the job of the dag processor\nand hasn\'t been involved in that flow since 2.0.\n\nTime to go.','2024-12-11 17:52:28','ashb'),(2978,'cc417216b2aca3dbe2ce8065cfe7dd4a93dc2a0b','19864447','Remove deprecated `kubernetes` commands from core (#44826)\n\nThese are deprecated in core and moved to the provider. We should remove\nthem for Airflow 3.','2024-12-11 17:45:24','jedcunningham'),(2979,'42dfa7eee1d4816dfb95863c7e472c250eb5765b','19864447','Small fix of system tests (#44815)\n\nCo-authored-by: Ulada Zakharava <vlada_zakharava@epam.com>','2024-12-11 13:50:02','VladaZakharova'),(2980,'cb74a41125ffbf0094c543b4f15110d378d7077f','19864447','Remove \"single process\" restrictions on SQLite in favour of using WAL mode (#44839)\n\nSince 2010(!) sqlite has had a WAL, or Write-Ahead Log mode of journalling\nwhich allos multiple concurrent readers and one writer. More than good enough\nfor us for \"local\" use.\n\nThe primary driver for this change was a realisation that it is possible and\nto reduce the amount of code in complexity in DagProcessorManager before\nreworking it for AIP-72 support :- we have a lot of code in the\nDagProcessorManager to support `if async_mode` that makes understanding the\nflow complex.\n\nSome useful docs and articles about this mode:\n\n- [The offical docs](https://sqlite.org/wal.html)\n- [Simon Willison\'s TIL](https://til.simonwillison.net/sqlite/enabling-wal-mode)\n- [fly.io article about scaling read concurrency](https://fly.io/blog/sqlite-internals-wal/)\n\nThis still keeps the warning against using SQLite in production, but it\ngreatly reduces the restrictions what combos and settings can use this. In\nshort, when using an SQLite db it is now possible to:\n\n- use LocalExecutor, including with more than 1 concurrent worker slot\n- have multiple DAG parsing processes (even before AIP-72/TaskSDK changes to\n  that)\n\nWe execute the `PRAGMA journal_mode` every time we connect, which is more\noften that is strictly needed as this is one of the few modes thatis\npersistent and a property of the DB file just for ease and to ensure that it\nit is in the mode we want.\n\nI have tested this with `breeze -b sqlite start_airflow` and a kicking off a\nlot of tasks concurrently.\n\nWill this be without problems? No, not entirely, but due to the\nscheduler+webserver+api server process we\'ve _already_ got the case where\nmultiple processes are operating on the DB file. This change just makes the\nbest use of that following the guidance of the SQLite project: Ensuring that\nonly a single process accesses the DB concurrently is not a requirement\nanymore!','2024-12-11 13:36:19','ashb'),(2981,'7f1d54ad4b14a4b255b20dfb162ee3667341d6f6','19864447','chore: remove deprecated bigquery facets from OpenLineage utils (#44838)\n\nSigned-off-by: Kacper Muda <mudakacper@gmail.com>','2024-12-11 13:33:50','kacpermuda'),(2982,'8480460da45e1e8fe7069ead1d0a936233b2d73a','19864447','Implement KubernetesInstallKueueOperator + (#44568)\n\nKubernetesStartKueueJobOperator and refactor GKE operatores','2024-12-11 13:13:41','moiseenkov'),(2983,'6ab06b3e093f991709681e65e53523949842e903','19864447','AIP-84 Standardize patch behavior across endpoints in fast api (#44619)\n\n* Add host_proxy_cmd parameter to SSHHook and SFTPHook\r\n\r\n* Standardize PATCH Behavior Across Endpoints in FastAPI\r\n\r\n* Revert \"Add host_proxy_cmd parameter to SSHHook and SFTPHook\"\r\n\r\nThis reverts commit 992cb61d89fc2265793a95de2e360777ba7c8d32.\r\n\r\n* fix the update_mask logic\r\n\r\n* Fixed connections file error and updated its unit test case\r\n\r\n* Fixed dag run file and updated its unit test case\r\n\r\n* Fixed dag file and updated its unit test case\r\n\r\n* Fixed variables file\r\n\r\n* Updated patch logic with alias=true\r\n\r\n* Added test cases and corrected dag logic','2024-12-11 12:44:44','ajitg25'),(2984,'1eb683be3a79c80927e9af1e89dabb5e78ce3136','19864447','Add ability to list active backfills both across cluster and per-dag (#44624)\n\n* Add ability to list active backfills both across cluster and per-dag (UI-only API)\r\n\r\n* Add ability to list active backfills both across cluster and per-dag (UI-only API)\r\n\r\n* Resolving PR comments\r\n\r\n* add alias\r\n\r\n* use filter_param_factory, change parameter name\r\n\r\n* use filter_param_factory, change parameter name\r\n\r\n---------\r\n\r\nCo-authored-by: Sneha Prabhu <snehaprabhu@Snehas-MacBook-Pro.local>','2024-12-11 11:46:51','prabhusneha'),(2985,'f0ec10e2f5283207c220ff2e21065e0c01454f6b','19864447','AIP-84 Add filter by da