ession` handling to FastAPI dependency system and use a normal session factory not a threadlocal one.\n\n![Screenshot 2024-11-19 at 16 06 47](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d5f1d5b5-9d10-4d34-9c96-4c01583c3a19)','2024-11-19 18:01:25','pierrejeambrun'),(3392,'c8c5756530b95de7f53b1f4cfc296d04627c7b25','19864447','Prepare FAB provider to set next version as major version (#43939)','2024-11-19 17:21:26','vincbeck'),(3393,'8d2e96f71ff6af22551665a04516eee82eef08c2','19864447','AIP-84 Fix: Allow Null Values for end_date Field in Dashboard Endpint in FastAPI (#44043)','2024-11-19 17:07:41','bugraoz93'),(3394,'7747b7b021133ea6e43bfc696fb7a6c75643275f','19864447','Fix failing mypy check on `main` (#44191)\n\nFailure on main:\r\n\r\n```\r\nproviders/src/airflow/providers/apache/spark/hooks/spark_submit.py:525: error:\r\nModule \"airflow.security.kerberos\" has no attribute \"get_kerberos_principle\";\r\nmaybe \"get_kerberos_principal\"?  [attr-defined]\r\n                from airflow.security.kerberos import (\r\n                ^\r\nproviders/src/airflow/providers/apache/spark/hooks/spark_submit.py:525: error:\r\nName \"get_kerberos_principal\" already defined (possibly by an import)\r\n[no-redef]\r\n                from airflow.security.kerberos import (\r\n                ^\r\nFound 2 errors in 1 file (checked 3337 source files)\r\nError 1 returned\r\n```','2024-11-19 16:52:47','kaxil'),(3395,'86c4c6fa9decd626cdea14aaf79d76252d4d7145','19864447','Migrate pickled data & change XCom value type to JSON (#44166)\n\nfollow-up of https://github.com/apache/airflow/pull/43905\n\nChanges:\n- Changed `XCom.value` column to JSON for all dbs.\n- Archived pickled XCom data to `_xcom_archive` and removed it from the `xcom` table.\n- Removed encoded string in XCom serialization and deserialization logic.\n- Updated logic for `XComObjectStorageBackend` to make it compatible for AF 2 & 3','2024-11-19 15:56:20','kaxil'),(3396,'39042c8c031ecb448a600e34367f8a899b15c8ea','19864447',